              <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">The Mechanism</p>
              <p class="apn-nutr-product-meta">Creatine monohydrate saturates intramuscular phosphocreatine stores over 3 to 4 weeks of daily use. Phosphocreatine is the immediate energy substrate for maximal efforts under 10 seconds. Higher PCr stores allow greater training loads before fatigue, which creates a larger MPS stimulus per session. Creatine also draws water into muscle cells, increasing cell volume and anabolic signaling.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#F8F8F8;padding:14px 16px;border-radius:3px;">
              <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#06A5C5;margin-bottom:6px;">Dose and Timing</p>
              <p class="apn-nutr-product-meta"><strong>5g daily</strong>, taken post-training or with a meal on rest days. Timing is not critical for creatine. Consistency is. Daily use for 28 days achieves full muscle saturation without a loading phase.</p>
