          <p class="apn-nutr-product-desc">5g daily without exception. At Champion tier, creatine consistency is non-negotiable and the timing is paired precisely with the post-training insulin spike.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STACK MISTAKE WARNING -->
      <div style="border-left:4px solid #F59E0B;background:#FFFBEB;padding:16px 20px;margin:24px 0;">
        <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:3px;color:#F59E0B;margin:0 0 8px;">Common Stack Mistake</p>
        <p style="font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:#333333;margin:0;line-height:1.65;">Using protein powder as a meal replacement instead of a protein distribution bridge. A shake is not a meal. It lacks the caloric density, micronutrient content, and satiety factors of whole food. Use it to hit leucine threshold when a full meal is not available, not as your primary eating strategy. Athletes who replace 2 or more meals per day with shakes often develop gut dysbiosis from inadequate dietary fiber, which further impairs protein absorption efficiency.</p>
